'''Shiroishi Kofun Group''' (白石古墳群, Shiroishi Kofun-gun) is a burial mound group located in {{ill|Fujioka City, Gunma Prefecture|ja|群馬県藤岡市}}. It dates from the early 5th century to the late 6th century and has been developed as the "Keno Province Shiroishi Hills Park" {{Sfn|Gunma Prefecture Fujioka City|url=https://www.city.fujioka.gunma.jp/kakuka/f_bunkazai/kenokuni0.html}}.
== Overview == The Shiroishi Kofun Group is distributed across Shiroishi, Kami-Ochiai, and surrounding areas in Fujioka City. It consists of four subgroups: the Nanakoshiyama Group, the Inariyama Group, the Saruta Group, and the Shimogo Group {{Sfn|Shinmura|2004|pages=294-297}}. The burial group began with the construction of the [[Shiroishi Inariyama Kofun]] on the terrace of the Ayukawa River and later expanded to include large-scale tombs and cluster mounds.
== Nanakoshiyama Group == * [[Nanakoshiyama Kofun]] * [[Isezuka Kofun (Fujioka)|Isezuka Kofun]] * Soneiji Higashi-Urazuka Kofun * Soneiji Nishi-Urazuka Kofun * [[Hirai District No. 1 Kofun]] * [[Oji-zuka Kofun (Fujioka)|Oji-zuka Kofun]] * Yakushi-zuka Kofun
== Saruta Group == * Saruta Kofun * Nabetsuka Kofun * Daimyodo Kofun * Hirose Kofun * Shiroyama Kofun
== Inariyama Group == * [[Shiroishi Inariyama Kofun]] * Jūnitensuka Kofun * Jūnitensuka Kita Kofun * Shinbori Otsuka Kofun
== Shimogo Group == * Taki No. 1 Kofun * Ehara-zuka Kofun * Horikoshi-zuka Kofun * Shiroishi Futago-yama Kofun * Hagiwara-zuka Kofun * Sahira-zuka Kofun
== Notes == {{脚注ヘルプ}} {{Reflist}}
== References == * {{Cite journal|ja|url=https://doi.org/10.15024/00001312|last=Shinmura|first=Tetsu|issue=120|title=Chapter 2: Geographical and Historical Environment of Sites (Part 2: Saruta II Site Investigation)|journal=Bulletin of the National Museum of Japanese History|publisher=[[National Museum of Japanese History]]|year=2004|DOI=10.15024/00001312|id={{CRID|1390853649019681536}}|date=2004-03-31|ref=harv}}
