'''Shiroishi Kofun Group''' (白石古墳群) is a group of {{ill|kofun|ja|古墳}} (burial mounds) located in {{ill|Fujioka, Gunma|ja|藤岡市}}, {{ill|Gunma Prefecture|ja|群馬県}}. It spans the 5th to late 6th centuries and is designated as part of the "Keno-no-Kuni Shiroishi Hills Park" (毛野国白石丘陵公園).<ref>{{Cite web|和書|author=Gunma Prefecture|url=https://www.city.fujioka.gunma.jp/kakuka/f_bunkazai/kenokuni0.html|title=Keno-no-Kuni Shiroishi Hills Park|accessdate=2023-01-14}}</ref>
== Overview == The Shiroishi Kofun Group comprises burial mounds in the Shiroishi, Kami-Ochiai, and other areas of Fujioka. It is divided into four subgroups: the Nanakoshiyama, Inariyama, Saruta, and Shimogo groups.<ref>{{Cite journal|和書|last=Shimura|first=Tetsu|title=Chapter 2: Geographical and Historical Environment of the Ruins (Part 2: Excavation of the Saruta II Site)|journal=Bulletin of the National Museum of Japanese History|volume=120|date=2004-03-31|DOI=10.15024/00001312}}</ref> The construction of the group began with the {{ill|Shiroishi Inariyama Kofun|ja|白石稲荷山古墳}} on the Ayukawa terrace, followed by the creation of massive tombs and cluster tombs. Detailed descriptions of each subgroup are provided below.
